senberg rohlen distinguished fellow at fsi spoke recently with cctv's world insight about the campaign and about china's soft power strategy noting the link between concern about china and uncertainty about the us economy world insight cctv china's image abroad search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest thomas fingar proposes some questions for the republican presidential debate november 17 2011 cisac fsi stanford shorenstein aparc announcement thomas fingar a new book explores the role of us intelligence august 17 2011 cisac fsi stanford announcement thomas fingar what does beijing think of us nuclear policy may 27 2011 cisac fsi stanford shorenstein aparc in the news thomas fingar beijing's soft power pr strategy february 15 2011 cisac in the news cctv thomas fingar discusses growth of china's global significance november 17 2010 shorenstein aparc news thomas fingar offers insights on intelligence and national security march 9 2009 fsi stanford cisac news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
